Fig. 3M
) divided into two sections by distinct transverse carina; carina produced anteromedially; anterior section narrowed anteriorly, partially fused with sixth sternite; posterior section with strongly raised lateral margins, bearing one pair of strong teeth anterolaterally; ventral surface depressed, with deep median pit followed by deep median groove extending to posterior surface.Eighth thoracic sternite (
Fig. 3M
) depressed medially on ventral surface.

